Explanation: The bug in the buggy code is in the round10 function. When the last digit of the number is 5 or more, it should add the difference between 10 and the last digit to the number, but the buggy code is adding the last digit to the number. This is why the buggy code will fail when the last digit of the number is 5 or more. Generated Test cases 1-10 (10/28) should pass the buggy code, as they have numbers with last digit less than 5. The rest of the test cases (11-28) should fail the buggy code as they have numbers with last digit 5 or more.
